    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Seeking Curbs On Executive Pay</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steve Talley letter says no one is worth hefty executive paychecks that have become commonplace (April 10 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Something is seriously wrong with capitalism in this country, and the world, if someone ''worth'' $950 per hour says that someone else is ''worth'' $19.4 million a year. (That is a compensation of $6,218 per hour, even assuming a 60-hour workweek.)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Something is seriously wrong with capitalism in this country, and the world, if someone ''worth'' $950 per hour says that someone else is ''worth'' $19.4 million a year. (That is a compensation of $6,218 per hour, even assuming a 60-hour workweek.)</p>
        <p>What can any human being on this earth possibly ''do'' to justify that much money? Reverse global warming? End religious strife? Halt hunger worldwide?</p>
        <p>Steve Talley  Portland, Ore., April 10, 2006</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
